Wolves are to rekindle interest in Leicester City striker Chris Wood next week when the loan window opens.

The Molineux club made a £1.25m bid for the New Zealand international last month but failed to agree personal terms.

Championship side Wolves are also looking to loan out defender Roger Johnson who saw a late move to Genk fall through last week.

